			"description": "Most endpoints require a JWT access token.\n\nAdd the token inside the Authorization header.\n\n``` bash\nAuthorization: Bearer <access_token>\n\n ```\n\n# User Roles\n\n| Role | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| ADMIN | Manage users and platform |\n| LANDLORD | Create and manage properties |\n| TENANT | Browse, rent and review properties |\n\n---\n\n# Standard Response Format\n\n### Success\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"statusCode\": 200,\n  \"message\": \"Request successful\",\n  \"data\": {}\n}\n\n ```\n\n---\n\n### Error\n\n``` json\n{  \n\"success\": false,  \n\"statusCode\": 400,\n\"message\": \"Something went wrong\",\n\"error\": {}\n}\n\n ```\n\n---"
		},
